sentences: Frances Blaisdell (January 5, 1912 – March 11, 2009) was an American flautist, widely recognized as one of the first female professional flautists.

In addition to playing, she also held teaching positions at the Manhattan School of Music, New York University, Dalcroze School, Mannes School of Music, and Stanford University where she taught for over 35 years.
Blaisdell was born in Tennessee on January 5, 1912, and was raised on a farm in Red Bank, New Jersey.
